==English==

===Etymology 1===
Shortened from ''Nelly Duff'', for ''puff'', supposedly meaning ''[[life]]''

====Proper noun====
'''Nelly'''

===Alternative spellings===
* [[Nellie]]
# A female [[given name]].

====Noun====
'''nelly''' (''not used in the plural'')
# (''[[Cockney rhyming slang]]'') [[Life]].

====Usage note====
*Used only in the phrase '''[[not on your nelly]]'''.

===Etymology 2===
From the noun meaning a homosexual man.

====Noun====
'''nelly''' (''plural:'' '''nellies''')
# (''derogatory slang'') An [[effeminate]] homosexual man.

====Adjective====
'''nelly''' (''[[comparative]]'' '''nellier''', ''[[superlative]]'' '''nelliest''')
#(''slang'') [[Unmanly]], effeminate.